{
  "Name": "Haz 8x2 SSCPGE | Scout Stationary Clear Practice Non-SP Scout Edition | R03",
  "Description": "
	Update:

		Buff non-stationary enemy spawn count.

	=======================================================================================

	Designed specifically for ground Scout solo stationary-clearing practice.

	Base Settings:

		4-player scaling.
		Based on StoneMason's 8x2.

	Adjustments:

		Adjust non-stationary enemy spawn.
		Buff projectile speed to CN Haz 8 level (2.3).
		Nerf Bulk resistance.
		Nerf Stalker resistance.
		Nerf Swarmer cap to 60.
		Nerf non-stationary enemy spawn count.
		Nerf non-stationary large enemy resistance.
		Resupply cost 40 Nitra.

	Rules:

		Bosco is recommended.
		Goal is clearing out high-threat stationaries; don't have to finish the mission.
		It is highly encouraged to actively kite the mobile enemies while simultaneously taking out the stationaries, rather than camping in a safe spot to clear the wave first and then safely shooting the stationaries. That being said, feel free to adjust your playstyle based on your current skill level.
		You can use Sandbox Utilities to resup yourself if you don't want to deal with Nitra RNG.
		You can teleport straight into the main cave and start clearing.
	
	Recommended Mods:

		Custom Mission: To select the exact mission type you want to practice on.
		Enemy Count: To monitor your clear progress and gauge the room's difficulty.
		Sandbox Utilities: To teleport through dirt and resup yourself.
	",
